SIMPLE: sunny
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sunny
<hw>Sun"ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Sunnier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Sunniest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to
the sun; proceeding from, or resembling the sun; hence, shining; bright;
brilliant; radiant.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Sunny</xex> beams.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Spenser.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Sunny</xex> locks.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Shak.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exposed to the rays of the sun; brightened or warmed
by the direct rays of the sun; <as>as, a <ex>sunny</ex> room; the
<ex>sunny</ex> side of a hill</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her blooming mountains and her <qex>sunny</qex> shores.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Cheerful; genial; <as>as, a <ex>sunny</ex>
disposition</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My decayed fair⟦br⟧
A <qex>sunny</qex> look of his would soon repair.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sunny</ent>⟦br⟧

